project.name: Dining Philosophers v1
project.description: In Dijkstra’s dining philosophers problem n philosophers sit around a table to have lunch. There are n plates, one for each philosopher, and n forks located to the left and to the right of each plate. Since two forks are required to eat the spaghetti on the plates, not all philosopher can eat at a time. Moreover, no communication except taking and releasing the forks takes place. The task is to devise a local strategy for each philosopher that lets all philosophers eventually eat. The simplest solution to access the left fork followed by the right one, has an obvious problem. If all philosopher wait for the second fork to be released there is no possible progress; a dead-end has occurred.

state.name: Holding right and left and Eat

action.precondition: p1.left = f and p2.right = f and p1.hungry = true and p2.hold->excludes(f)
action.postcondition: p1.hasLeft = true and p1.hold = p1.hold->including(f) and p1.hungry = false

action.precondition: p1.right = f and p2.left = f and p1.hasLeft = true and p2.hold->excludes(f)
action.postcondition: p1.hasLeft = false and p1.hold = p1.hold->including(f) and p1.eat = true

action.precondition: p.eat = true and p.hold->includes(f) and p.left = f
action.postcondition: p.hold = p.hold->excluding(f) and p.eat = false and p.hasRight = true

action.precondition: p.hold->includes(f) and p.right = f and p.hasRight = true
action.postcondition: p.think = true and p.hold = p.hold->excluding(f) and p.hasRight = false
